						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">loopy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Disch wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- In the case of "lda (NZPV),Y", I'd think the best course of action would be either:<br /> --  give an error and refuse to assemble<br />or<br /> --  assemble as truncated (take low byte only) and give a warning that the value was truncated</div><br />I would argue that truncating an address will ALWAYS give you the wrong thing, so it should be an error, not a warning.</div>
<br />
<br />Good point.  Great discussion.</div>

