					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Not sure whether my reply got hidden in the shuffle, but I posted a disambiguation syntax that should already work on all assemblers:
<br />
<br />lda (NZPV)+0,y ; abs,y
<br />lda 0+(NZPV),y ; abs,y (alternate syntax)
<br />
<br />With this "syntax", you can treat lda (NZPV),y as illegal (since NZPV&gt;$FF).</div>

